The paper deals with compressive sensing in the context of MIMO radar, which involves signal processing, information theory, and statistical signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed framework in terms of system-level metrics such as resolution and number of degrees of freedom, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper deals with the coherence of measurement matrices, which is a topic in linear algebra and optimization, and hence could be classified under cs.SP (Signal Processing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
